                <h4>System Modelling </h4>

    
              <p>3 credits of System Modelling tools from the following:</p>
    
              <ul class="program-set">
                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/esys-301" class="program-course-title">
              ESYS 301 Earth System Modelling (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-25442" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Earth &amp; Planetary Sciences (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/615">Faculty of Science</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Earth System Science              : Principal concepts of systems modelling related to earth system science and environmental science. Students explore the ideas of state, stability, equilibria, feedbacks, and complexity using simple models.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Winter 2015          </p>

